How football&#39;s financial rules will affect Neymar&#39;s move to Paris
Rules aimed at preventing unlimited spending by European football clubs will not prevent Neymar&#39;s world-record transfer from Spain&#39;s Barcelona to France&#39;s Paris Saint-Germain.
Whatever the consequences may come down the chain, for Paris Saint-Germain from UEFA, the governing body that controls European football, which has the power to ban teams from the prestigious Champions League tournament.
Financial fair play rules introduced by UEFA in 2011 suggest that PSG will eventually have to show that Neymar&#39;s transfer was financed without major losses.
Barcelona were paid 222 million euros ($262 million) just to release the Brazilian from his contract, and Neymar will receive a salary that will reach tens of millions of dollars a year.
