Shadow Minister of Public Health Sharon Hodgson said: &quot;We very much welcome the start of the PrEP trial, which is very late due to months of delays and procrastination by the government.&quot;
The data demonstrates how revolutionary this drug can be as part of our approach to preventing HIV and stopping the transmission of this fatal infection.
This trial will bring us one step closer to fully understanding the benefits of PrEP.
